01:24:58,844 --> 01:25:00,972
- Did Teddy send you?
- I don't know.

953
01:25:02,556 --> 01:25:05,226
- What's happened to Jimmy?
- I don't know that either.

954
01:25:05,309 --> 01:25:07,687
- Sorry.
- You don't remember anything?

955
01:25:07,770 --> 01:25:11,107
You don't remember where you've been
or what you've just done.

956
01:25:11,190 --> 01:25:14,819
No. I can't make new memories.
Everything just fades.

957
01:25:14,902 --> 01:25:17,613
- Then why did you come here?
- I found this in my pocket.

958
01:25:20,908 --> 01:25:22,410
<i>Your</i> pocket.

959
01:25:47,059 --> 01:25:50,187
Bar bet. Care to contribute?

960
01:25:50,271 --> 01:25:52,606
- No, thanks.
- It's for a lot of money.

961
01:25:53,190 --> 01:25:56,152
Come on. Proceeds are going to charity.
Help me out.

962
01:26:08,414 --> 01:26:09,707
Thank you.

963
01:26:27,141 --> 01:26:29,226
- On the house.
- Thanks.

964
01:26:34,023 --> 01:26:36,400
It's completely fucked
because nobody believes you.

965
01:26:37,610 --> 01:26:40,863
It's amazing what a little brain damage
will do for your credibility.

966
01:26:40,946 --> 01:26:43,741
I guess it's some kind of poetic justice
for not believing Sammy.

967
01:26:43,824 --> 01:26:45,993
You know the truth about my condition, Officer?

968
01:26:46,827 --> 01:26:48,829
You don't know anything.

969
01:26:48,913 --> 01:26:51,082
You feel angry, you don't know why.

970
01:26:51,165 --> 01:26:53,918
You feel guilty, you have no idea why.

971
01:26:54,752 --> 01:26:57,380
You could do anything and not have
the faintest idea 10 minutes later.

972
01:26:57,463 --> 01:26:59,840
Like Sammy.
What if I've done something like Sammy?

973
01:27:00,549 --> 01:27:03,803
I didn't tell you what happened
to Sammy and his wife?

974
01:27:05,554 --> 01:27:08,724
She came to see me at my office. I thought
she was trying to catch me off guard…

975
01:27:08,808 --> 01:27:11,727
<i>so I didn't tell her what I really thought,
but I never said that he was faking…</i>

976
01:27:11,811 --> 01:27:13,729
<i>just that his condition was mental,
not physical.</i>

977
01:27:13,813 --> 01:27:16,774
<i>I found out later that she went home
and gave Sammy his final exam.</i>

978
01:27:18,484 --> 01:27:21,445
Sammy? It's time for my shot.

979
01:27:37,419 --> 01:27:39,421
<i>She knew beyond a doubt that he loved her.</i>

980
01:27:40,589 --> 01:27:42,550
<i>So she found a way to test him.</i>

981
01:27:55,271 --> 01:27:58,858
Sammy. It's time for my shot.

982
01:28:08,826 --> 01:28:10,870
<i>She really thought she'd call his bluff.</i>

983
01:28:10,953 --> 01:28:12,454
There you go.

984
01:28:13,038 --> 01:28:16,876
<i>Or she just didn't wanna live
with the things she'd put him through.</i>

985
01:28:26,844 --> 01:28:27,845
Sammy.

986
01:28:30,014 --> 01:28:32,141
It's time for my shot.

987
01:28:37,605 --> 01:28:39,398
It won't hurt.

988
01:29:23,526 --> 01:29:25,569
<i>She went into a coma and never recovered.</i>

989
01:29:26,737 --> 01:29:29,823
<i>Sammy couldn't understand
or explain what happened.</i>

990
01:29:32,117 --> 01:29:34,036
He's been in a home ever since.

991
01:29:34,119 --> 01:29:36,538
<i>He doesn't even know that his wife is dead.</i>

992
01:29:36,622 --> 01:29:40,000
I was wrong about Sammy,
and I was wrong about his wife.

993
01:29:40,084 --> 01:29:42,002
She wasn't interested in the money.

994
01:29:42,086 --> 01:29:44,255
She just needed to understand his problem.

995
01:29:44,338 --> 01:29:47,758
<i>His brain didn't respond to conditioning.
But he wasn't a con man.</i>

996
01:29:47,841 --> 01:29:51,262
<i>When she looked into his eyes,
she thought he could be the same person.</i>

997
01:29:51,345 --> 01:29:53,722
<i>When I looked into his eyes,
I thought I saw recognition.</i>

998
01:29:53,806 --> 01:29:55,933
Now I know. You fake it.

999
01:29:56,016 --> 01:29:58,852
If you think you're supposed to
recognize somebody, you just pretend to.

1000
01:29:58,936 --> 01:30:01,605
<i>You bluff it to get a pat
on the head from the doctors.</i>

1001
01:30:02,231 --> 01:30:04,483
You bluff it to seem less of a freak.

1002
01:30:08,112 --> 01:30:09,757
What drug dealer?

1003
01:30:35,222 --> 01:30:38,350
- Hey, Lenny, how you doing?
- It's private back here.

1004
01:30:38,434 --> 01:30:41,437
- It's okay. We know each other. Right, kid?
- How did you know I was in here?

1005
01:30:41,520 --> 01:30:43,522
The Jag's out front.
Should have put it around back.

1006
01:30:43,605 --> 01:30:47,109
What are you still doing here, Lenny?
There's plenty of tattoo parlors up north.

1007
01:30:47,192 --> 01:30:49,695
I guess I wanted to get something down
before it slipped my mind.

1008
01:30:49,778 --> 01:30:52,239
- Give me the keys. I'll move it.
- It'll be all right for a minute.

1009
01:30:52,323 --> 01:30:53,824
Wait out there.

1010
01:30:54,658 --> 01:30:57,244
Give me a minute.
I gotta get something for you.

1011
01:31:00,998 --> 01:31:05,044
Fact six: Car license SG137IU.

1012
01:31:11,091 --> 01:31:13,344
Look. Wait a minute, will ya?

1013
01:31:16,847 --> 01:31:18,891
- We gotta get you out of here.
- Why?

1014
01:31:18,974 --> 01:31:22,269
Man. Come on, Leonard.
How many times I gotta tell you?

1015
01:31:22,353 --> 01:31:24,730
- It's not safe for you to hang around here anymore.
- Why not?

1016
01:31:24,813 --> 01:31:26,732
Because that cop's looking for you.

1017
01:31:26,815 --> 01:31:29,401
I gotta get you a new identity,
some new clothes.

1018
01:31:29,485 --> 01:31:32,112
A different car would do for now.
So put these on.

1019
01:31:32,196 --> 01:31:33,572
What cop?

1020
01:31:34,782 --> 01:31:37,743
He's a bad cop. He's the one
that checked you into the Discount Inn.

1021
01:31:37,826 --> 01:31:41,663
He's been calling you for days, telling you shit,
slipping envelopes under your door. Shit like that.

1022
01:31:41,747 --> 01:31:44,458
- How do you know this?
- He told me. He thinks it's funny.

1023
01:31:44,541 --> 01:31:46,543
- He's been laughing at you.
- You're full of shit.

1024
01:31:46,627 --> 01:31:49,463
I'm not. He knows you're no good on the phone,
so he's been calling you.

1025
01:31:49,546 --> 01:31:51,548
Sometimes you don't answer the phone…

1026
01:31:51,632 --> 01:31:54,426
so he slips shit under your door to scare you
into answering the phone again…

1027
01:31:54,510 --> 01:31:57,179
giving you a line of crap about John G.
being some local drug dealer.

1028
01:31:57,262 --> 01:32:00,516
- Jimmy Grants.
- Who's Jimmy Grants?

1029
01:32:00,599 --> 01:32:02,559
Leonard, Jimmy's the drug dealer.

1030
01:32:02,643 --> 01:32:04,937
The cop wants to know how his operation's run.

1031
01:32:05,020 --> 01:32:07,022
He's got some score in mind.
Somehow you're involved.

1032
01:32:07,106 --> 01:32:08,774
Uh-huh. How do you know him?

1033
01:32:09,858 --> 01:32:14,571
I'm a snitch. He's a cop from out of town.
The local boys put us together.

1034
01:32:14,655 --> 01:32:16,990
If he knew I was helping you,
he'd fucking kill me.

1035
01:32:17,074 --> 01:32:20,869
So take these clothes, put them on
and get the fuck out of here.

1036
01:32:20,953 --> 01:32:23,580
Come on, Leonard. Just go.

1037
01:32:44,226 --> 01:32:46,186
You are full of shit.

1038
01:32:47,896 --> 01:32:50,065
“Come by after. Natalie.”

1039
01:32:50,149 --> 01:32:51,650
“Ferdy's Bar.”

1040
01:33:34,485 --> 01:33:35,819
Hey, Jimmy.

1041
01:33:38,864 --> 01:33:41,658
I'm sorry.
I thought you were somebody else.

1042
01:33:42,326 --> 01:33:43,660
Sorry.

1043
01:33:44,495 --> 01:33:45,746
That's okay.

1044
01:33:59,927 --> 01:34:03,180
So this Jimmy Grants deals drugs out of the bar
where his girlfriend works?

1045
01:34:04,014 --> 01:34:06,517
But he's not gonna bring her along.
He'll come by himself, right?

1046
01:34:07,851 --> 01:34:10,812
I always figured the drugs angle
would be the best way to get him.

1047
01:34:11,855 --> 01:34:15,025
No, Officer. I'm as ready as I'll ever be.

1048
01:34:15,734 --> 01:34:18,278
You're in the lobby? What do you look like?

1049
01:34:19,571 --> 01:34:21,532
I'll be right there.

1050
01:35:03,657 --> 01:35:04,575
Lenny.

1051
01:35:07,703 --> 01:35:08,912
Officer Gammell.

1052
01:35:11,456 --> 01:35:14,167
Yeah. Come on.

1053
01:35:30,684 --> 01:35:33,145
- Smile.
- Not here.

1054
01:35:34,479 --> 01:35:35,772
Over here.

1055
01:35:41,445 --> 01:35:44,448
- Is it Officer or Lieutenant Gammell?
- You know what?

1056
01:35:44,531 --> 01:35:46,742
Don't write Gammell, just Teddy.

1057
01:35:47,409 --> 01:35:49,453
- Why?
- I'm undercover.

1058
01:35:52,289 --> 01:35:54,708
This is the directions where he's going.

1059
01:35:54,791 --> 01:35:57,836
- My number's on the bottom if you need me.
- You're not coming?

1060
01:35:57,920 --> 01:35:59,838
No. It wouldn't be appropriate.

1061
01:36:04,384 --> 01:36:07,471
Nice picture. I look thin.

1062
01:36:11,183 --> 01:36:12,476
Hey, Lenny.

1063
01:36:13,143 --> 01:36:14,561
Make him beg.

1064
01:37:37,644 --> 01:37:38,895
Teddy!

1065
01:37:42,107 --> 01:37:43,608
Hey, Teddy!

1066
01:37:50,574 --> 01:37:51,742
Jimmy.

1067
01:37:53,535 --> 01:37:56,121
- What the fuck are you doing here?
- You Jimmy Grants?

1068
01:37:56,204 --> 01:37:58,206
Expecting any other Jimmys out here,
Memory Man?

1069
01:37:58,290 --> 01:38:02,544
- Do you remember me?
- Yeah, I remember you.

1070
01:38:02,627 --> 01:38:05,046
Where the fuck's Teddy?

1071
01:38:05,130 --> 01:38:05,839
Well?

1072
01:38:09,968 --> 01:38:12,763
Motherfuck-Fuckin' retard!

1073
01:38:14,890 --> 01:38:17,934
- Strip.
- You're making a big fucking mistake, pal.

1074
01:38:18,018 --> 01:38:19,311
Strip!

1075
01:38:21,396 --> 01:38:23,982
My associates are not
the kind of people you wanna piss off.

1076
01:38:24,065 --> 01:38:25,650
Don't say anything else.

1077
01:38:25,734 --> 01:38:28,153
- I knew I couldn't trust that fuck!
- Take it off.

1078
01:38:30,781 --> 01:38:32,324
Cocksucker.

1079
01:38:33,408 --> 01:38:35,202
Your pants too.

1080
01:38:36,161 --> 01:38:38,121
- Why?
- I don't wanna get blood on them.

1081
01:38:40,207 --> 01:38:42,209
Wait. Did he tell you what I was bringing?

1082
01:38:42,292 --> 01:38:46,213
- Take your fuckin' pants off!
- I've got 200 grand stashed in the car!

1083
01:38:46,296 --> 01:38:49,007
- Just take it!
- You think you can bargain with me?

1084
01:38:49,091 --> 01:38:51,468
- Take the money and walk away!
- I don't want your fuckin' money.

1085
01:38:52,511 --> 01:38:53,970
Then what?

1086
01:38:54,513 --> 01:38:58,183
- What do you want from me?
- I want my fuckin' life back!

1087
01:40:28,773 --> 01:40:29,983
Sammy.

1088
01:40:36,781 --> 01:40:38,825
He said “Sammy.”
How does he know about Sammy?

1089
01:40:38,909 --> 01:40:40,285
Oh, fuck.

1090
01:41:00,889 --> 01:41:02,891
What have I done?

1091
01:41:04,768 --> 01:41:07,479
Mister, I need help.
There's a guy in here, he's hurt bad.

1092
01:41:07,562 --> 01:41:09,814
- We gotta get him to a doctor.
- All right.

1093
01:41:11,608 --> 01:41:13,902
I don't know what happened.
I've got this memory thing.

1094
01:41:13,985 --> 01:41:16,196
- Do I know you?
- No. Don't worry. I'm a cop.

1095
01:41:17,030 --> 01:41:19,824
- Is he still breathing?
- I don't know. Maybe.

1096
01:41:19,908 --> 01:41:22,452
What the hell were you guys
doing down here?

1097
01:41:23,995 --> 01:41:26,081
I don't remember. I have this condition.

1098
01:41:26,164 --> 01:41:28,875
I hope it's not as serious as his,
'cause this guy's dead.

1099
01:41:28,959 --> 01:41:31,503
Ow! Lenny! That shit kills!

1100
01:41:31,586 --> 01:41:35,131
So you remember me now, huh?
You are a fuckin' cop.

1101
01:41:35,215 --> 01:41:38,051
Yeah. And I'm the guy
that helped you find him.

1102
01:41:38,134 --> 01:41:40,011
Get up. Get up.

1103
01:41:40,095 --> 01:41:42,138
Lenny, you got the wrong idea.

1104
01:41:44,849 --> 01:41:46,893
Who is that? He knew me.

1105
01:41:46,977 --> 01:41:49,604
Of course he did. He raped your wife.
He fucked up your brain.

1106
01:41:49,688 --> 01:41:51,731
Bullshit. He's not the guy.

1107
01:41:51,815 --> 01:41:56,152
His name is James F. Grants.
John G. Check your tattoos.

1108
01:41:56,236 --> 01:41:58,655
- What was he bringing the 200 grand for?
- What?

1109
01:42:00,240 --> 01:42:03,034
- What was it for?
- A load of amphetamines I told him I had.

1110
01:42:03,118 --> 01:42:06,579
- Is this a drug deal?
- No. Yeah, that and your thing.

1111
01:42:06,663 --> 01:42:10,291
Look, Leonard, Jimmy's your guy. I just
figured we'd make a few dollars on the side.

1112
01:42:10,375 --> 01:42:14,004
- How did he know me?
- The Discount Inn. He dealt out of there.

1113
01:42:14,087 --> 01:42:17,382
The guy at the front desk let him know
if anybody came snooping around.

1114
01:42:17,465 --> 01:42:20,010
He called Jimmy the minute he saw you
taking a picture of the dump.

1115
01:42:20,093 --> 01:42:22,470
- You're fucking using me.
- No! You get half!

1116
01:42:22,554 --> 01:42:25,181
He knew about Sammy!
Why would I tell him about fuckin' Sammy?

1117
01:42:25,265 --> 01:42:28,643
You tell everybody about Sammy,
everybody who'll listen.

1118
01:42:28,727 --> 01:42:30,854
“Remember Sammy Jankis?”
“Remember Sammy Jankis?”

1119
01:42:30,937 --> 01:42:33,857
Great story.
Gets better every time you tell it.

1120
01:42:34,816 --> 01:42:36,735
So you lie to yourself to be happy.

1121
01:42:36,818 --> 01:42:38,862
There's nothing wrong with that.
We all do it.

1122
01:42:38,945 --> 01:42:42,073
Who cares if there's a few little details
you'd rather not remember?

1123
01:42:44,534 --> 01:42:46,870
- What the fuck are you talking about?
- I don't know.

1124
01:42:47,662 --> 01:42:49,581
Your wife surviving the assault.

1125
01:42:50,373 --> 01:42:52,292
Her not believing your condition.

1126
01:42:52,375 --> 01:42:56,546
The torment and pain and anguish
tearing her up inside.

1127
01:42:57,130 --> 01:42:58,423
The insulin.

1128
01:42:59,716 --> 01:43:02,427
That's Sammy, not me.
I told you about Sammy.

1129
01:43:02,510 --> 01:43:05,513
Yeah, right.
Like you tell yourself over and over again.

1130
01:43:05,597 --> 01:43:07,599
Conditioning yourself to remember.

1131
01:43:07,682 --> 01:43:10,268
- Learning through repetition.
- Sammy let his wife kill herself.

1132
01:43:10,351 --> 01:43:15,398
- Sammy ended up in an institution.
- Sammy was a con man, a faker.

1133
01:43:15,482 --> 01:43:17,650
I never said that Sammy was faking.

1134
01:43:18,234 --> 01:43:20,695
You exposed him for what he was-a fraud.

1135
01:43:20,779 --> 01:43:22,739
But I was wrong. That's the whole point.

1136
01:43:24,407 --> 01:43:27,160
- See, Sammy's wife came to me.
- Sammy didn't have a wife.

1137
01:43:29,913 --> 01:43:32,248
It was <i>your</i> wife who had diabetes.

1138
01:43:38,630 --> 01:43:39,631
Ouch.

1139
01:43:42,258 --> 01:43:43,927
My wife wasn't diabetic.

1140
01:43:44,928 --> 01:43:46,346
You sure?

1141
01:43:51,142 --> 01:43:54,270
- Ouch. Cut it out.
- She wasn't diabetic.

1142
01:43:55,271 --> 01:43:59,067
You think I don't know my own wife?
What the fuck is wrong with you?

1143
01:43:59,150 --> 01:44:02,570
I guess I can only make you remember
the things you wanna be true.

1144
01:44:02,654 --> 01:44:05,031
- Like old Jimmy down there.
- He's not the right guy.

1145
01:44:05,115 --> 01:44:07,283
He was to you.

1146
01:44:07,367 --> 01:44:10,787
Come on. You got your revenge.
Enjoy it while you still remember.

1147
01:44:10,870 --> 01:44:13,373
What difference does it make
whether he was your guy or not?

1148
01:44:13,456 --> 01:44:16,084
- It makes all the difference.
- Why? You're never gonna know.

1149
01:44:16,167 --> 01:44:17,460
- Yes, I will.
- No, you won't.

1150
01:44:17,544 --> 01:44:19,003
I will. Somehow I'll know.

1151
01:44:19,087 --> 01:44:21,506
- You won't remember!
- When it's done, I will know. It'll be different.

1152
01:44:21,589 --> 01:44:25,510
I thought so too.
In fact, I was sure of it, but you didn't!

1153
01:44:28,304 --> 01:44:31,558
That's right. The real John G.

1154
01:44:31,641 --> 01:44:35,228
I helped you find him over a year ago.
He's already dead.

1155
01:44:35,311 --> 01:44:38,189
- Don't lie to me anymore.
- Look, Lenny.

1156
01:44:38,815 --> 01:44:41,693
I was the cop assigned to your wife's case.
I believed you.

1157
01:44:41,776 --> 01:44:44,320
I thought you deserved a chance for revenge.

1158
01:44:44,404 --> 01:44:47,699
I'm the one that helped you find the other guy
in your bathroom that night…

1159
01:44:47,782 --> 01:44:50,118
the guy that cracked your skull
and fucked your wife.

1160
01:44:50,201 --> 01:44:52,662
We found him. You killed him.

1161
01:44:54,330 --> 01:44:59,669
But you didn't remember.
So I helped you start looking again…

1162
01:44:59,752 --> 01:45:02,005
looking for the guy you already killed.

1163
01:45:02,547 --> 01:45:04,299
Yeah? So who was he?

1164
01:45:04,382 --> 01:45:06,759
Just some guy. Does it even matter who?

1165
01:45:07,510 --> 01:45:11,389
No reason, Lenny. No conspiracy.
Just bad fucking luck.

1166
01:45:12,599 --> 01:45:16,352
Couple of junkies too strung out
to realize your wife didn't live alone.

1167
01:45:17,520 --> 01:45:21,316
But when you killed him,
I was so convinced that you'd remember.

1168
01:45:21,900 --> 01:45:23,860
But it didn't stick.

1169
01:45:23,943 --> 01:45:26,696
Like nothing ever sticks.
Like this won't stick.

1170
01:45:31,367 --> 01:45:35,997
I took that picture… just when you did it.

1171
01:45:37,999 --> 01:45:39,918
Look how happy you are.

1172
01:45:41,252 --> 01:45:43,004
I wanted to see that face again.

1173
01:45:43,087 --> 01:45:45,882
- Gee, thanks.
- Fuck you.

1174
01:45:45,965 --> 01:45:49,719
I gave you a reason to live,
and you were more than happy to help.

1175
01:45:49,802 --> 01:45:53,973
You don't want the truth.
You make up your own truth.

1176
01:45:54,057 --> 01:45:56,017
Like your police file.

1177
01:45:56,851 --> 01:45:59,854
It was complete when I gave it to you.
Who took out the 12 pages?

1178
01:45:59,938 --> 01:46:02,482
- You, probably.
- No, it wasn't me. See, it was you.

1179
01:46:02,565 --> 01:46:06,277
- Why would I do that?
- To create a puzzle you could never solve.

1180
01:46:06,361 --> 01:46:08,279
You know how many towns?

1181
01:46:08,363 --> 01:46:10,532
How many John G.'s or James G.'s?

1182
01:46:10,615 --> 01:46:12,659
Shit, Lenny. I'm a fucking John G.

1183
01:46:12,742 --> 01:46:15,995
- Your name is Teddy.
- My mother calls me Teddy.

1184
01:46:16,079 --> 01:46:18,957
My name's John Edward Gammell.

1185
01:46:19,040 --> 01:46:20,083
Cheer up.

1186
01:46:20,166 --> 01:46:22,919
There's plenty of John G.'s for us to find.

1187
01:46:26,297 --> 01:46:28,716
All you do is moan.

1188
01:46:28,800 --> 01:46:31,135
I'm the one that has to live
with what you've done.

1189
01:46:31,219 --> 01:46:32,929
I'm the one that put it all together.

1190
01:46:33,012 --> 01:46:37,684
You wander around, you're playing detective.
You're living a dream, kid.

1191
01:46:37,767 --> 01:46:41,854
A dead wife to pine for.
A sense of purpose to your life.

1192
01:46:41,938 --> 01:46:45,275
A romantic quest that you wouldn't end
even if I wasn't in the picture.

1193
01:46:46,568 --> 01:46:49,737
- I should kill you.
- Quit it. Lenny, come on.

1194
01:46:49,821 --> 01:46:52,824
You're not a killer.
That's why you're so good at it.

1195
01:46:56,369 --> 01:46:59,122
What are you doing?
You know what time it is?

1196
01:46:59,205 --> 01:47:01,291
It's beer o'clock. I'm buying.

1197
01:47:03,293 --> 01:47:04,419
Fuck.

1198
01:47:14,512 --> 01:47:15,638
I'm not a killer.

1199
01:47:16,931 --> 01:47:19,475
I'm just someone who wanted
to make things right.

1200
01:47:25,523 --> 01:47:27,900
Can I just let myself forget
what you've told me?

1201
01:47:45,126 --> 01:47:48,504
Can I just let myself forget
what you made me do?

1202
01:48:02,769 --> 01:48:04,520
You think I just want another puzzle to solve?

1203
01:48:05,355 --> 01:48:07,523
Another John G. to look for?

1204
01:48:08,733 --> 01:48:10,610
You're a John G.

1205
01:48:12,320 --> 01:48:14,405
So you can be my John G.

1206
01:48:22,872 --> 01:48:24,999
Do I lie to myself to be happy?

1207
01:48:26,292 --> 01:48:28,044
In your case, Teddy…

1208
01:48:29,170 --> 01:48:31,089
yes, I will.

1209
01:48:44,227 --> 01:48:46,312
Hey, that's not your car!

1210
01:48:46,396 --> 01:48:48,981
- It is now.
- Jesus Christ, you can't take it!

1211
01:48:49,065 --> 01:48:51,984
- Why not?
- Because the guy you just killed owns it!

1212
01:48:52,068 --> 01:48:53,778
Somebody'll recognize it!

1213
01:48:55,238 --> 01:48:58,324
I think I'd rather be mistaken
for a dead guy than a killer.

1214
01:48:59,283 --> 01:49:01,786
I might hang on to this for a while.

1215
01:49:02,620 --> 01:49:03,913
Lenny.

1216
01:49:05,957 --> 01:49:08,459
Will you help me find the keys?

1217
01:49:08,543 --> 01:49:10,294
Help me find my keys.

1218
01:49:32,567 --> 01:49:35,862
I have to believe in a world
outside my own mind.

1219
01:49:35,945 --> 01:49:38,114
I have to believe that
my actions still have meaning…

1220
01:49:38,197 --> 01:49:40,158
even if I can't remember them.

1221
01:49:42,326 --> 01:49:44,996
I have to believe
that when my eyes are closed…

1222
01:49:45,079 --> 01:49:47,165
the world's still here.

1223
01:49:48,374 --> 01:49:50,793
Do I believe the world's still here?

1224
01:49:53,713 --> 01:49:55,298
Is it still out there?

1225
01:49:59,135 --> 01:50:00,136
Yeah.

1226
01:50:02,513 --> 01:50:05,308
We all need mirrors
to remind ourselves who we are.

1227
01:50:07,643 --> 01:50:09,353
I'm no different.

1228
01:50:22,658 --> 01:50:24,452
Now, where was I?